AS A SEISMOLOGIST,

66
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,800
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT
UNDERWATER EARTHQUAKES

67
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,800
ARE THE CAUSE
OF THESE TIDAL WAVES?

68
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,200
THE TSUNAMI. UH,
IT'S TOO EARLY TO TELL.

69
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,000
WELL,
2 IN A ROW LIKE THIS,

70
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
ISN'T THAT UNUSUAL?

71
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,600
YES, YES,
MOST UNUSUAL.

72
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,800
EXCUSE ME, PLEASE.

73
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,800
BUT--DOCTOR, EXCUSE ME.

74
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,600
THE INVITED SCIENTISTS
ARE BEING MET

75
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:03,600
BY THE INSTITUTE'S

76
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,200
ASSOCIATE RESEARCH
DIRECTOR...

77
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,200
DR. WAHL?

78
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,000
I'M MARLAN CLARK.
THIS IS FRANK BRISICK.

79
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,800
HOW DID YOU KNOW
WHERE I WAS?

80
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,200
OH, WE'VE ALWAYS KNOWN.

81
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,600
MORE OR LESS.

82
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,000
WELL, YOU CAN
GO BACK AND TELL THEM

