00:26:57,800 --> 00:27:00,400
YOU ARE JUST DARING HIM TO
POINT THE FINGER AT YOU. WHY?!

483
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,400
JUST GET AWAY FROM ME!

484
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,600
YOU'VE GOT THE KNOW-HOW
TO MAKE THESE WAVES HAPPEN.

485
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:06,000
DO YOU THINK I WOULD DO
SOMETHING LIKE THIS

486
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,000
TO ANYONE?

487
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,000
MY DOG IS DEAD!

488
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:09,800
MY HOUSE IS--

489
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:10,800
I DON'T KNOW.
PICK IT OUT!

490
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:12,800
IS IT THERE?!
IS IT THERE?!

491
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,400
I'M LUCKY TO BE ALIVE.

492
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,000
YOU CAN DROP THAT IDEA

493
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:49,000
OF SOMEBODY USING ANY KIND
OF BOMB TO DO THIS.

494
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,400
WHAT MAKES YOU SO SURE?

495
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,600
WAHL! I'M STUMBLING
AROUND IN THE DARK HERE,

496
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,600
AND YOU ACT LIKE
YOU KNOW EVERYTHING.

497
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,000
I DON'T KNOW DIDDLY,

498
00:27:57,400 --> 00:28:00,400
BUT I WAS INVOLVED
IN OFFSHORE NUCLEAR TESTING.

499
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:03,600
YEAH, WE WERE TRYING
TO MAKE A TIDAL WAVE.

500
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,400
AND I CAN TELL YOU THIS.

501
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:06,400
AN EXPLOSION,
ESPECIALLY A NUCLEAR ONE,

502
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:09,600
IS A BAD WAY TO DO IT.
IT'S ALL HEAT.

503
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:12,000
THE DISPERSED WATER
EVAPORATES.

504
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,800
THERE'S GONNA BE A WAVE,

505
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:14,800
BUT BY THE TIME
IT HITS THE SHORE,

506
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,200
IT'S GONNA BE
DOWN TO NOTHING.

507
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,800
IF IT CAN'T BE DONE,

508
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:19,800
WHY DO THEY THINK
YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE?

509
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:24,600
'CAUSE I WAS GETTIN' CLOSE
TO THE WAY IT COULD BE DONE.

510
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:28,000
COULD BE DONE,
DR. WEAVER.

511
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:31,200
NOBODY KNEW
HOW CLOSE I WAS.

512
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,800
I DIDN'T DO IT, WEAVER!
I GOT OUT!

513
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,200
I BUILT MYSELF
A NICE LITTLE SCENARIO.

514
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,400
I SLUGGED A GUY
AT DEFENSE,

515
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:45,200
I DUG MYSELF A HOLE,
AND I JUST DROPPED THROUGH.

516
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,800
I DON'T CARE ABOUT
ANYTHING ANYMORE!

517
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:51,600
THEY CAN ALL BLOW
THEMSELVES UP FOR ALL I CARE.

518
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:57,200
I GOT OUT...
AND I WANT TO STAY OUT.

519
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:18,600
HE WANTS ME
TO TRY AND FIND HIM.

520
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,200
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

521
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:25,000
WHOEVER THE HELL
IS DOING THIS.

522
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:27,000
THE PHONE CALL,
THE LETTER.

523
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:30,200
IT'S AN INVITATION.

524
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:32,600
"FIND ME."

525
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:34,600
THEN DO IT.

526
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:36,600
GIVE ME SOME TIME.

527
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:38,200
I WILL.

528
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,400
MAYBE I CAN
BUY YOU SOME.

529
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:48,800
COME ON.

530
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:03,800
AQUATRONICS.

531
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,400
IT'S JESSICA WEAVER.

532
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:07,600
LET ME SPEAK
WITH DR. PURCELL.

533
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,200
PURCELL.

534
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:12,400
EDGAR?

535
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:14,600
I JUST CAME FROM THE BEACH.

536
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:15,600
JOHN WAHL'S MISSING.

537
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:19,200
HE WAS THERE, BUT, UH,
NOT ANYMORE.

538
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:20,000
WHO, EXACTLY,
SAID HE WAS--

539
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:22,000
LET ME SUGGEST YOU PUT
SOME OF THE OTHERS

540
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:24,800
UNDER THE SAME MICROSCOPE
YOU'VE GOT LOCKED ON WAHL.

541
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:26,800
WE ALREADY ARE,
DR. WEAVER.

542
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:29,600
THANK YOU FOR SHARING
YOUR THOUGHTS.

543
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,200
EDGAR, I HOPE YOU'RE
LOOKING FOR MORE THAN

544
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:35,600
HOW HE'S DOING IT.

545
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:38,400
GO HOME, DR. WEAVER.

546
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:44,400
THE BASTARD.

547
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:46,000
YEAH. WELL,

548
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,400
LET'S NOT FORGET THAT
HE'S THE TOP BASTARD.

549
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:52,800
OH, JEEZ.

550
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,800
YOU'VE GOT TO LET ME
LOOK AT THAT ARM.

551
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:56,400
HEY, HEY...

552
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,400
JUST DRIVE.

553
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,600
EARLIER TODAY,

554
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:03,000
THE PRESIDENT FLEW OVER
THE DISASTER AREA

555
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:04,600
AND LATER MET
WITH SURVIVORS

556
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:06,600
TO PERSONALLY EXPRESS
HIS SYMPATHY.

557
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:07,800
IN A SEPARATE STATEMENT,

558
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:11,000
THE WHITE HOUSE HAS ASKED
ALL AMERICANS TO REMAIN CALM.

559
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,600
THIS SO-CALLED
CONFERENCE, MR. CLARK,

560
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:14,600
WHY, EXACTLY,
DID THEY CALL IT?

561
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,600
MR. PURCELL
HAS ALREADY DECIDED

562
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,600
THAT JOHN WAHL
IS RESPONSIBLE

563
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:19,400
FOR WHAT IS HAPPENING.

564
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:21,800
I DON'T THINK HE HAS.

565
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:24,600
AH. SO IT'S NOT
JOHN WAHL.

566
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:26,400
IT'S ONE OF US.

567
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,800
YOU THINK
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

568
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:29,400
ON THE CONTRARY,

569
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,800
EVERY ONE OF US HAS
CONSIDERED THE POSSIBILITY

570
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:32,400
OF CONTROLLING
SUCH A NATURAL POWER.

571
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,800
THIS PLACE, THIS AQUATRONICS,

572
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:36,200
RECEIVES SO MUCH MONEY
FROM THE GOVERNMENT

573
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:37,800
BECAUSE TO HARNESS THE OCEANS

574
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:42,000
WOULD MAKE EVERYONE
PAY ATTENTION.

575
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:46,800
SO IT IS QUITE POSSIBLE
THAT ONE OF US IS DOING IT.

576
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,400
NOT I, OF COURSE.

577
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,200
WOULD YOU RELAX, WAHL?

578
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,600
I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.

579
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:56,600
I HAD
2 YEARS OF PREMED.

580
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:59,600
THEN WHAT?
TALK TO ME, COMMANDER.

581
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:01,600
ABOUT WHAT?

582
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,200
YOU ARE SUCH A SISSY.
YOU'RE AFRAID TO WATCH.

583
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:06,200
YEAH, WHEN IT COMES
TO ME, YES, I AM.

584
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:08,200
ALL RIGHT, YOU DID
A COUPLE OF YEARS PREMED,

585
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:09,200
THEN WHAT?

586
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:11,200
DON'T GIVE ME ONE
OF THOSE PRINTOUT RESUMES.

587
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:12,200
YOU KNOW,

588
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:13,600
"I WENT TO AFGHANISTAN
UNDER COVER OF BLAH BLAH."

589
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:16,600
OK, OK, I SEE
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

590
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:19,200
WELL, MY FATHER
WAS NAVY...

591
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,200
KOREA?

592
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,200
MM-HMM.

593
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,200
I WAS BORN

594
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:24,600
AFTER HE CAME BACK
AND RETIRED.

595
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,600
HE WAS A LOT OLDER
THAN MOM.

596
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,600
I GREW UP
LOVING THE WATER.

597
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:29,600
OW!

598
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,600
OK. OK,
I'M FINISHED.

599
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:31,600
WHAT DID YOU--

600
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:34,200
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
JEEZ.

601
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:36,600
WELL, YOU WANT TO
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS?

602
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:40,600
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

603
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:41,600
IT'S NICE STITCHING.

604
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:42,600
THANKS.

605
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:44,600
YOU DO GOOD WORK.

606
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:47,600
WELL, WE BETTER GET
YOU SOME CLOTHES.

607
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,600
OHH...

608
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:53,000
THEY'RE ALAN'S.

609
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:55,000
I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO GET RID OF THEM,

610
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,600
BUT AREN'T YOU GLAD
I DIDN'T?

611
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,600
THRILLED.

612
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:01,000
IT'S A LITTLE...
SNUG FOR YOU?

613
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,600
HE ACTUALLY WORE
THIS STUFF?

614
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:04,000
LOOK, I THINK I'M
JUST GOING TO

615
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:05,600
WASH MY OWN CLOTHES.
YOU DO HAVE

616
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:06,600
A WASHING MACHINE
AROUND HERE, WEAVER?

617
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,000
YES, I DO,

618
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,600
AND THE NAME
IS JESSIE.

619
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:12,800
STILL GOT YOUR HUSBAND'S
CLOTHES, HUH?

620
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,400
I FIND THAT KIND OF
INTERESTING.

621
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:15,800
NO, IT'S NOT.
THEY'RE JUST CLOTHES.

622
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:16,800
NO.

623
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:18,400
THEY'RE
ALAN'S CLOTHES.

624
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:19,800
GUESS YOU STILL GOT

625
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:22,800
SOMETHING THERE
FOR HIM, HUH?

626
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:24,200
THERE IS NOTHING THERE.

627
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,200
YOU KNOW, EITHER WAY,

628
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,800
IT'S REALLY NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.

629
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:28,200
YOU'RE RIGHT,
I'M SORRY.

630
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,200
IT'S OK.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

631
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:30,200
FORGET IT.
I'M SORRY.

632
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:31,200
I'LL SEE YOU
LATER.

633
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:32,200
WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?

634
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:33,200
AQUATRONICS,
REMEMBER?

635
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:34,200
AND DON'T USE
THE PHONES.

636
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:35,200
YOU THINK
THEY'D BUG YOU?

637
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:36,800
I KNOW THEY WOULD.

638
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,200
TRY NOT TO BURN DOWN
THE HOUSE

639
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:39,200
WHILE I'M GONE, WAHL.

640
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:41,800
IT'S JOHN.

641
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:43,800
JOHN.

642
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,800
JOHN WAHL AND
JESSICA WEAVER.

643
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:47,200
HEY!

644
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:49,200
WE HAVE
THE SAME INITIALS.

645
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:50,800
CLEVER.

646
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:00,400
YOUNG JOHN WAHL
WAS BRILLIANT.

647
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,400
UNPREDICTABLE.

648
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,200
IDEALISTIC.

649
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:07,800
JUST YOUR
REGULAR SCIENTIST.

650
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:10,200
I WAS THERE
WHEN HE, UH...

651
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:13,400
WHEN THAT INCIDENT WITH
THE UNDERSECRETARY HAPPENED.

652
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,800
AND, UH, I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S JUST A FEELING I HAD.

653
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:18,200
AS A MATTER OF FACT,

654
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:19,800
I HAD THE SAME FEELING
AGAIN THE OTHER DAY

655
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:21,800
WHEN I SAW HIM.

656
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:23,600
WHAT FEELING WAS THIS,
DR. SCHIFF?

657
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:26,000
THE REASON WE THOUGHT
HE TOOK OFF AND QUIT.

658
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:28,200
NO, I DON'T THINK
THAT WAS IT.

659
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:30,000
I THINK IT WAS
SOMETHING ELSE.

660
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,400
I THINK...

661
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,200
I THINK IT WAS
SOMETHING HE FOUND.

662
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:35,000
SOMETHING HE WANTED
TO KEEP TO HIMSELF.

663
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,800
TO HIMSELF...

664
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,400
OR FOR HIMSELF?

665
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:43,600
I'M NOT COMFORTABLE WITH
THAT SUGGESTION, MR. CLARK.

666
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:53,800
I CAN'T EVEN GET CLOSE
TO THEIR FILES.

667
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,000
WAHL?

668
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,600
RIGHT HERE.
AAH! GOD...

669
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:59,000
SORRY. I'M SORRY.

670
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:01,600
ALL RIGHT, EVERYTHING IS
ALL CLEAR OUT BACK, I THINK.

671
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,000
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

672
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,400
ZIP. I THOUGHT I
COULD PATCH THROUGH

673
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:07,000
TO THE AQUATRONICS
MAINFRAME,

674
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,400
BUT
IT'S BLOCKING ME.

675
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:09,800
LET ME TRY
SOMETHING ELSE.

676
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,800
I COULDN'T GET
TO THEIR FILES

677
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,600
BECAUSE THEY WERE
RIGHT THERE ALL DAY.

678
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,200
EDGAR WALKING AROUND

679
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:16,400
LOOKING
OVER MY SHOULDER.

680
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:18,200
AGAMO WAS USING THE
MAINFRAME COMPUTER.

681
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,800
THE MINUTE
HE FINISHED,

682
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:21,000
BERNARD NETWORKED IT

683
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,000
OVER TO THE WAVE ROOM
TO USE IT.

684
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,000
ALL RIGHT,
LOOK AT THIS.

685
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:27,800
THE SURF
FROM THE OTHER DAY.

686
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,000
HOW'D YOU MAKE
THAT HAPPEN?

687
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:31,400
THE WEATHER SERVICE
HAS EVERY WEATHER PATTERN

688
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:34,200
TRANSLATED INTO
NUMBERED COORDINATES.

689
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:35,200
ADD AN ALGORITHM...

690
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,200
MM-HMM.

691
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,000
YOU GET IT IN PICTURES.

692
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:39,800
LOOK.

693
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:43,000
THIS MORNING'S WAVE.

694
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:44,200
SOMEWHERE...

695
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:47,000
THERE HAS TO BE
A GROUND ZERO.

696
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,200
I KNOW.

697
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:49,800
WELL, LET'S FIND IT.

698
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:50,600
NO. I MEAN,

699
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,200
THIS IS WHAT BERNARD
WAS WORKING ON.

700
00:35:52,200 --> 00:35:53,200
HE HAD IT UP ON THE
WAVE ROOM MONITORS.

701
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:54,200
TODAY?

702
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,600
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING.

703
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:56,600
BERNARD WAS LOOKING
THROUGH THIS?

704
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:58,200
HE STILL IS.
HE STAYED BEHIND

705
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:01,400
BECAUSE HE THOUGHT
HE WAS ON TO SOMETHING.

706
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:08,400
MAY I ASK YOU
SOMETHING?

707
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,600
IF YOU'RE CREATING WAVES,

708
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:12,000
AND YOU WANT TO KEEP
ANYBODY FROM FINDING OUT

709
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:13,800
WHERE THEY ORIGINATED,
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

710
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:18,000
FIND THE ONE COMPUTER
THAT WOULD SHOW YOU HOW.

711
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,200
BERNARD?

712
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:23,000
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

713
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,800
IT MAKES SENSE.

714
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:27,800
WHEN WE WERE WORKING
ON WAVES,

715
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,800
WE WERE WORKING FROM
MATHEMATICAL MODELS

716
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:32,400
THAT HE CREATED.

717
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:34,400
YEAH, BUT...

718
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:35,400
HE'S NICE.

719
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:36,800
YOU SAID SO
YOURSELF.

720
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:40,800
YEAH, HE'S ONE OF
THE REAL DARLINGS

721
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,800
OF THE THEORETICAL
SCIENCES, JUST LIKE ME.

722
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:47,800
BUT YOU STILL
SUSPECT ME...

723
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,400
DON'T YOU?

724
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,000
WELL, HE MUST BE GONE.

725
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,600
DO YOU SMELL SOMETHING?

726
00:37:22,600 --> 00:37:23,800
LET ME TURN THE LIGHT ON.

